The paper discusses data-driven decision-making algorithms for non-stationary bandit settings, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA) to some extent, which are less likely but still relevant sub-categories.
